        outputStream.writeObject(game.clone());
        outputStream.flush();
        System.out.println(&quot;SERVER:\tObject sent&quot;);
    }
```

The Game Class now needs to implement the Cloneable interface and save the things you want to save in your Game Class clone (or at least how you want to clone it):

```
    @Override
    public Game clone() throws CloneNotSupportedException {
        Game clone = (Game) super.clone();
        clone.teams = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
        for (Team team : teams) {
            clone.teams.add(team.clone());
        }
        clone.playingField = playingField.clone();
        clone.numPlayers = numPlayers;
        clone.gameIsRunning = gameIsRunning;
        clone.currentlyPlaying = currentlyPlaying.clone();
        clone.lastDiceRoll = lastDiceRoll;
        clone.firstRun = firstRun;
        clone.numBots = numBots;
        clone.difficulty = difficulty;
        return clone;
    }
```

If your Game Class is referencing other classes, they need to be cloned as well (and therefor also have to implement the Cloneable interface).

